Summary: This section explains variable assignment and type flexibility in GDScript compared to statically typed languages.
Variables & assignment
All variables in GDScript are dynamically typed, meaning their type is not fixed and can change through assignment.

GDScript:
    var a # 'null' by default.
    a = 5 # Valid, 'a' becomes an integer.
    a = "Hi!" # Valid, 'a' changed to a string.
