Path: godot/tutorials/scripting/gdscript/gdscript_advanced.rst
Summary: This section explains how GDScript arrays differ from arrays in statically typed languages, highlighting their dynamic nature and ability to hold mixed data types.

GDScript arrays are dynamic and can hold mixed data types, unlike static arrays which are fixed in type and size.

GDScript:
```gdscript
var array = [10, "hello", 40, 60] # You can mix types.
array.resize(3) # Can be resized.
use_array(array) # Passed as reference.
# Freed when no longer in use.
```

GDScript arrays can also function as lists:

GDScript:
```gdscript
var array = []
array.append(4)
array.append(5)
array.pop_front()
```

And as unordered sets:

GDScript:
```gdscript
var a = 20
if a in [10, 20, 30]:
    print("We have a winner!")
```
---CHUNK---
